description
overview of the position
the commercial data science officer cdso lead a department of 30+ data scientist predictive modeler and data engineer in support of the hartfords commercial property casualty and group benefits business unit the cdso partner with business leader to develop and execute a strategic roadmap for data science that advance our business goal and creates competitive advantage through the use of data and analytics this requires becoming deeply familiar with the strategic direction of each business unit it marketplace and the driver of profitable growth the cdso is accountable for data science resource optimization best practice and project prioritization execution delivery and monitoring of result s he is also expected to be a driving force in the implementation of analytical insight tool and model working across organizational boundary
the focus of the commercial data science team is on improving our pricing and underwriting capability through the use of advanced data and analytical capability for all commercial property casualty and group benefits insurance product including commercial auto business owner package policy property general liability worker compensation group short and long term disability and group life insurance
the cdso lead the commercial data science team in pursuit of new insight to better understand the risk attribute behavioral characteristic and predictor of loss outcome for prospect and customer s he will expand the use of third-party data asset and in combination with the hartfords proprietary data develop new and innovative approach for risk evaluation exposure development customer segmentation and the analysis of customer attribute to provide insight on the driver of financial and physical loss s he will also provide leadership on the development and implementation of cutting-edge advanced analytic tool to produce scalable automated analytical process and solution this requires the cdso to engage with external firm including large established enterprise a well a start-up company to identify and harness new capability that can be used to develop competitive advantage for the hartford
this role requires close partnership with the hartfords enterprise data office which is accountable for our enterprise data strategy governance and delivery in addition the cdso will serve a a critical member of various executive team and steering committee a we continue to evolve our enterprise-wide data and analytics discipline from both a strategy and talent perspective
responsibilities
manage the day-to-day work of the data science team ensuring that project achieve appropriate milestone and that status and result are communicated to the business partner in a clear concise fashion
ensure model are properly implemented with the highest level of buy in from internal customer this would include supporting work such a customer pricing dislocation analysis compliance challenge communication material and monitoring plan
pioneer new research methodology expand our analytical tool and increase our use of new data source to capture opportunity for business growth
ensure continuous improvement and innovation see that our tool and capability use the newest technology available improve our timeline in term of speed to market always be looking for additional external source of data and additional variable that can upgrade our existing toolkit
partner with business customer and other thought leader to identify research and or business opportunity that the data science team can support and help develop
be a strategic thought partner with the business helping to advance our overall strategic goal by identifying supporting data science project opportunity that may pay dividend in the long term
oversee develop and train staff and consultant provide direction and assistance on an ongoing basis to ensure group ha knowledge and technical experience to execute against stated agenda
